This implementation establishes a "Zero-Touch" automated feedback loop. It removes the need for customers to manually copy/paste tokens and instead uses your Google Drive as a secure, temporary landing zone (The Inbox) for incoming data.

### 1. The Google Apps Script (The Bridge)
To make this work, you must create a script in your Google account that acts as the "Receiver." 
1. Open [script.google.com](https://script.google.com).
2. Create a "New Project" named **AEWorks Feedback Relay**.
3. Replace the code with this specific version designed to handle "Simple" POST requests:

```javascript
/**
 * AEWorks Feedback Relay v1.1
 * Handles cross-origin feedback submission from the Customer Portal.
 */
function doPost(e) {
  const folderName = "AEWORKS_INBOX";
  const folders = DriveApp.getFoldersByName(folderName);
  const folder = folders.hasNext() ? folders.next() : DriveApp.createFolder(folderName);

  // Parse incoming content (sent as text/plain to avoid CORS preflight)
  const data = JSON.parse(e.postData.contents);
  const timestamp = new Date().getTime();
  const fileName = "FB_" + (data.code || "UNKNOWN") + "_" + timestamp + ".json";

  folder.createFile(fileName, e.postData.contents, MimeType.PLAIN_TEXT);

  return ContentService.createTextOutput("RECEIVED")
    .setMimeType(ContentService.MimeType.TEXT);
}
```
4. **Deploy** > **New Deployment** > **Web App**.
5. Set **"Execute as"** to **Me** and **"Who has access"** to **Anyone**. 
6. Copy the **Web App URL** and update it in `PublicFeedbackPortal.tsx`.

### 2. The Feedback Lifecycle
*   **Public Portal:** When the client clicks "Sign," it now sends a `POST` request with the JSON payload. We use `text/plain` content-type. This is a technical trick to avoid "CORS Preflight" errors, ensuring the request succeeds even from a different domain without complex server configuration.
*   **The Inbox Folder:** The script saves a `.json` file in a folder named `AEWORKS_INBOX` on your Drive.
*   **Automated Pickup:** Every 2 minutes (or when you refresh), the Manager App checks this folder. If it finds a file matching a project code (e.g., `AEP-AUT-001`), it imports the feedback into that project and **immediately deletes the file from Drive** to keep your inbox clean.
*   **Feedback Journal:** A new module on your dashboard aggregates all these reviews into a single list, sorted by date, allowing you to track company-wide performance trends.

### 3. Visual Implementation
*   **Dashboard Alerts:** The "Feedback" card on your Landing Page now features a pulsing amber badge if there are "Received" feedbacks waiting for your verification.
*   **Project Board:** Cards for projects with new feedback will pulse to grab your attention.

